com.metreeca.form.shapes

Class Datatype

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.metreeca.form.shapes.Datatype
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Shape

    public final class Datatype
extends Object
implements Shape
    Datatype value constraint.

    States that each term in the focus set has a given extended RDF datatype.

    For validation purposes IRI references and blank nodes are considered to be respectively of Form.IRIType and Form.BNodeType datatype.

    • Method Detail

      • datatype

        public static Datatype datatype(IRI iri)
        Creates a datatype constraint.

        Beyond literal datatypes, the following extend values are supported:

        • Form.BNodeType for blank nodes;
        • Form.IRIType for IRI references;
        • Form.ResourceType for blank nodes or IRI references;
        • Form.LiteralType or RDFS.LITERAL for any literal.
        Parameters:
        iri - the expected extended datatype
        Returns:
        a new datatype constraint for the provided iri
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if iri is null
